The paper focuses on learning equivariant representations in convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed method involves applying rotation transformations on filters, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on image classification tasks, which is a common application in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
